The (possibly complex) parameter Ï„ is called the seed frequency. In Algorithm 1, we state the
global GMRES method [13]. Note that in the block Arnoldi method the trace inner product is
used, and norms are replaced by the Frobenius norm Â·F for block matrices. After m iterations,
an approximate solution to (2) in the block Krylov subspace Km (AP (Ï„ )âˆ’1 , B) is obtained.

